fg_segments: Football-Italia.net respects your rights to privacy and to choose what information you would like to receive or give.
The nature of the service provided by Football-Italia.net means that we may obtain certain information about you.
Football-Italia.net only collects Personally Identifiable Information (PII) that is freely provided by you and are necessary for the provision of our services.
Unless a visitor willingly supplies PII, we do not know who they are.
We may keep a record of the email address and message content of any web user who contact us by email.
We will use your information to improve the delivery of our service and make it more relevant to you.
We will not sell or make available in any way your personal information.
At all times we have security measures and technical safeguards in place to prevent unauthorised access, theft or loss of any information.
Our employees are aware of and accountable for compliance with these procedures.
If you would like to opt-out of any data gathering and analysis by Football-Italia.net you can do so by using the links in our cookie policy page, which can be found here.

Please note that whilst you can opt-out of sharing information for our 3rd party advertising/behavioural cookies, your continued use of the site will be viewed as acceptance of our 1st party cookies necessary for the functionality and analytics for Football-Italia.net.
Please be aware that if you choose to opt-out of interest-based ads, it does not mean you will no longer see advertising on Football-Italia.net.
It means we will no longer be able to deliver ads that are tailored to your interests, or to limit the number of times you see the same ad on different web pages.
As a result, you may start to see the same ad over and over again and/or see ads that have no relevance to you.
This privacy policy is subject to change without notice.
We may change our privacy policy at any time by posting a new version of it on our website.
Each version of this privacy policy will be identified by its effective date.
For more information, or if you have any questions or concerns regarding Football-Italia.net privacy policy, please contact us directly at editorial@calcioitalia.co.uk.

raw_html:
Privacy Policy

	Football-Italia.net respects your rights to privacy and to choose what information you would like to receive or give. The nature of the service provided by Football-Italia.net means that we may obtain certain information about you. Football-Italia.net only collects Personally Identifiable Information (PII) that is freely provided by you and are necessary for the provision of our services.

	Unless a visitor willingly supplies PII, we do not know who they are. We may keep a record of the email address and message content of any web user who contact us by email.

	How is my information used?

	We will use your information to improve the delivery of our service and make it more relevant to you. We will not sell or make available in any way your personal information.

	How secure is my information?

	At all times we have security measures and technical safeguards in place to prevent unauthorised access, theft or loss of any information. Our employees are aware of and accountable for compliance with these procedures.

	What cookies do you use?

	You can find details on our cookie use here.

	How do I opt-out?

	If you would like to opt-out of any data gathering and analysis by Football-Italia.net you can do so by using the links in our cookie policy page, which can be found here. Please note that whilst you can opt-out of sharing information for our 3rd party advertising/behavioural cookies, your continued use of the site will be viewed as acceptance of our 1st party cookies necessary for the functionality and analytics for Football-Italia.net.

	Please be aware that if you choose to opt-out of interest-based ads, it does not mean you will no longer see advertising on Football-Italia.net. It means we will no longer be able to deliver ads that are tailored to your interests, or to limit the number of times you see the same ad on different web pages. As a result, you may start to see the same ad over and over again and/or see ads that have no relevance to you.

	Changes to our privacy policy

	This privacy policy is subject to change without notice. We may change our privacy policy at any time by posting a new version of it on our website. Each version of this privacy policy will be identified by its effective date.

	Effective date

	This privacy policy was last revised on 09/07/2012.

	Contacting us

	For more information, or if you have any questions or concerns regarding Football-Italia.net privacy policy, please contact us directly at editorial@calcioitalia.co.uk.
